reviews.text: Small yet insightful.  Very affordable.
Very informative, a good introduction to the town before exploring downtown.
Great place to learn about the past and teach kids.. and a family place.

Good little museum. Right at the Crossroads of the railroads. Houses some Civil War artifacts and of course train station artifacts. It is inside an old train depot. Staff was very friendly and  helpful. When we were there we were the only people going through the museum at that time.
Great place to start exploring the town
Very beautiful historical property.
Make sure to take the guided tour.
A great historic location to have a party, wedding or gathering.  The history of the Curlee House is wonderful in itself!
Beautiful place to visit
They do great work. Bit better watch it, they love to sell you stuff LOL
James Cooper made for great experience. Friendly, knowledgeable and a gentleman.

I have a 2017 pioneer 1000 purchased from lake hill where I purchased a 2 year extended warranty the unit started grinding and jumping when put in low gear. Brought it to the service department they said that was how all units shifted the transmission is not right. So I wonder if they want the transmission to go out after my warranty goes out so they want be on the hook for it. Disappointed is an understatement from honda and lake hill!
Great and friendly service. Fast and easy
They were very rude and wanted to power sale me as soon as they were told that I was not going to do anything that day their salesman blew me off

Afforable local art. Very nice operators.
The Coliseum is a great venue. No bad seats. Good acoustics.

Best country food place around and they are quick and the buttermilk pie is awesome!!!
Good hot food at great price

I feel being in the customer service profession you need to know how to speak to people on general. I had no idea this place even existed till today we went to eat lunch next door. I told my husband I wanted to try it next. The parking is very confusing downtown and I will admit we did not park correctly. We parked next to a truck and thought it was acceptable. We parked got our infant son out and went in to eat next door to this place. Before our drinks even get to our table. The owner of this establishment opened the door and started talking to us with such disrespect I couldn't even believe it. My truck and the truck we parked next to were blocking her drive through. I didnt know there was even one we apologized and moved our truck but she threatened to call the cops and cause a scene and was just plain disrespectful. You lost us and everyone in the place we were eating buisness. Learn common respect. And just so everyone knows the end of the story. The police said we were not parked illegally she could be as mad as she wanted we didnt have to move. But we did because we have decency.
Good food.
Nice food, good service, quaint atmosphere!

We really liked it. Great breakfast and atmosphere. Just good southern cooking and people. Unfortunately,  after 25 years, they closed for good on September 16, 2018. I visited for the first and only time the day before.

This is an Awesome place!  Home cooked meals,  like Granny would cook.
The staff is also beyond great.  Makes ya feel right at home.  
VERY CLEAN !, I ASKED TO SEE THE KITCHEN!!!  I WILL FREQUENT HERE !!!
This was fantastic food. Great service. Friendly atmosphere. I will definitely make another trip here. Thank you Martha’s Menu.
The food was extremely good, the service was in a timely manner. The price of the food was great
Great southern comfort food, excellent service!
Hostess was rude, waitress was subpar. The food, which I have loved in the past was horrible. The fries were cold, the soup was cold and drinks were never refilled.
Great food, service and very reasonable prices. Family works hard to make your visit great!
Something about the way the menu is priced makes me feel like it's high, but it's really not. The food is decent enough.
We had a party of 25+ and the service was excellent. Food was delicious.
Good food & Great Environment & wonderful staff!
It surprises me how it is always full. By no means spectacular and more often than not, disappointing when you are looking for something curated. Even during non-peak times you'll have a bit to wait.

This has to be, by far, the best restaurant I've ever been to. My boyfriend and I went and it was so awesome. From the beginning, our hostess was incredible. She was a middle aged blonde lady and was very outgoing and friendly. Then, our waiter. A younger male, he was very polite and helpful. He seemed to know his way around and helped us with our order. He checked back at our table twice to see if we needed anything. When my drink was halfway empty, he grabbed it and filled it without any communication which was cool. A manager came around and made sure we were all enjoying our food. The food itself was also awesome. Overall it was great. I wish I could have told the owner how wonderful it was, everyone there did an awesome job and we thoroughly enjoyed it. We visited on 3/17/19 around 11 A.M. Hopefully the owner can see this and know they have a really awespme crew.
This is a wonderful place. Great atmosphere and good food to boot.
Excellent food AWESOME service and PRICES.. we will be back.  Thank you.
Amazing place, people, and food. We travel over 3 hours to eat here. Look forward to next time.
First experience was great. Good catfish, good shrimp, really enjoyed the fried pickles. Wife had chicken Alfredo and said it was as good as she's had anywhere. Will be back again.

Great service, friendly, gator was the best, the rest of the food was kind of bland. My shrimp was good but spicy. Booth tables are sticky but we sat at a regular table because of that. Still decent food.
This is a unique little place with good food. The quality is consistent. It's just a neat little place to eat...Good for family dining.😍
Great food & great service...as always.
Wonderful shrimp salad ! I'll be back they were really busy ! But food is awesome that's why!!

Very well worth the wait!!! The salad bar was on point, beautiful green salad fresh and well stocked. The gentleman cleaning tables was amazing very friendly and hard worker. Our waitress was very awesome always made sure our drinks were full and she was always smiling. The steaks were the best I've had in a very long time!!! If your looking for a tender juicy steak this is the perfect place!!!!

This is absolutely the best steak we've ever had! My wife and I drive from Florence, AL as often as possible....1 or 2 times a month to get their delicious steaks!!  Yes, it is crowded and you better get there early and get in line but WOW, it's worth the wait! Thanks Russell's!!

High Profit Restaurant- Poor Quality Food. I ordered the 16 oz Sirloin Steak.  The grade of meat was average at best. The meat was tough, dry, and full of fat. The steamed veggies as a side consisted of 4 green beans, 3 pieces of broccoli, 5 carrot slices , 4 very small pieces of pepper, and a microscopic slither of squash. The salad bar was extremely limited. They make sure to tell you only ONE trip to the salad bar.  My dinner was $19.95 for such poor quality and i left hungry. It's obvious this restaurant makes high profits because of the low expense for junky food and robbing the customers.  NEVER AGAIN will i stop at this joke of a steakhouse.

We love the salad bar here. It has a pretty solid variety of toppings and dressings. The sweet potatoes are usually massive and their sugar / cinnamon mix is good.

The steak has been hit or miss in terms of how it’s cooked. That’s my only complaint. It’s a big part of the meal though, so that’s why I have to go for 3 star.

Very cozy, hometown type of restaurant. Small salad bar with fresh vegetables and good selection. The garlic bread will melt in your mouth. I ordered the 18oz ribeye, medium rare cause that's how God intended steak to be cooked, and it was great. I honestly think it was close to 20oz, but either way it was way better than most ribeyes. If you want to get a real steak instead of the cookie cutter steakhouse experience this is the place.

If your looking for a tender juicy steak this is the perfect place!!!!

No longer Corner Slice, now it's Firebirds. Wish they had more light food for those that are on a diet.
Little high for the size of the calzone. However it was very delicious. Worth it in my book. Will stop here again for sure!
Always supper nice. Loved in Corinth me whole life. Every time I go in there, the food is great!
Great place ! Amazing crust
Stopping off in Corinth  (so the wife could antique shop) and wanted a quick bite...it was after 2pm and the owner opened the doors and made me a pie...got to love small town USA.

One of the best Pizza Huts in the area. First folks in so the buffet wasn’t completely out yet. Though the food that was, was absolutely delicious & hot. Staff was friendly & on top of things. Restaurant was pretty clean & well organized.
SO so ummy...and I love supporting young readers -- thanks, Hut! ...did I mention how very yummy the pizza was? Seriously. Good pizza 🥰
Love their pizza! It's the best anywhere. The service at this one is amazing, too!
Food was good and so was the service. Waitress was great also!
Pizza hut has been always the best pizza and love the salads and sauces. Great services as well.
Sam was my server and she did a great job. The food was good and at a good price. Definitely will be coming back more :)

The food was absolutely great and the service couldn’t have been any better! Everything was brought to me in a mannerly order and timely too. I will definitely be coming back. Ms. Kaitlyn laughed and cut up with me! During my visit last night I had the greatest time! She was the absolute sweetest!! The store was clean and kept up nicely. Thanks for the food!!

I've come in a couple times and haven't had the greatest experience, the service was terrible and the rotel was burnt. But I was in the area trying to get a quick bite and thought let me give them one more chance, because the third times a charm right? And it definitely was! Cortney was wonderful she gave the best service, and the food was great today. Thank you for changing around my previous experience.

I was in town visiting with my family,  we had lunch at sweet peppers one of the days and was not disappointed.  I had a loaded potato and broccoli and cheese soup and my husband had the shrimp flat bread we loved it all! The service was great , Cortney did such a great job taking care of us.

Never been here before but came in with my husband for lunch  yesterday. The food was really really good, as well as our service from Mrs.Cortney. Cortney even offered us a free desert because it was our first time eating here! We will definitely be back, thank you for a great experience

Picked up some take out. I had the Mongolian Beef with steamed rice and hot & sour soup. The soup was delicious and on the spicy side. Rice was nice and fluffy and I asked for a little cup of the “red sweet/sour sauce” as I like to put it on the rice. They were happy to accommodate my request.
The Mongolian Beef was outstanding! It was still piping hot when I opened the carton at home. The meat was tender and full of flavor. Best I’ve had in town. Will definitely order from them again.

I have a very mixed opinion of this place. Im giving three stars only because the food is always great, fresh, etc which is why I keep going back. HOWEVER, the service in house is subpar. Staff always seems frustrated that you are there and it takes FOREVER to get your food. So only go if you are not in a hurry to be anywhere soon. As far as calling in, good luck. That’s hit or miss. Some days I can get an answer and other days I never am able to get anyone to pick up the phone, and yes- I am calling during their funky business hours. Also, if you call in, still expect it to take at least 30 minutes or more for your food to be ready to be picked up.
Food not to bad.
We love this place. Been following that s business for over 20 years.
Nice Thai food, and inexpensive.

This awesome place has my business! The waiter suggested the Chino Pollo, I hope I spelled that right. No disrespect at all. This dish was great with the chicken and Mexican sausage. Love it! Can't wait to go back!
The food was delicious, but I went with my family and we didn't get enough chips, salsa, or napkins to keep my toddler clean.

The buffet is absolute trash, dont let these people lie to you. Theirs like 10 items and its never fresh, like ever. Ate there couples weeks ago and i had almost finished eating before i even got my drink. Lol
Great buffet. Jose is a great guy. When u ready to join the Army call Tom
Love the buffet! Excellent price.

Wonderful authentic food for a good price. Plus the manager/owner was very nice and helpful and went over the menu, and created a memorable time and also have vegetarian options for anyone wanting something healthy. Keep up the good work!!
Whenever we visit Corinth, we need to eat here.  Food is always superb. Service with a smile.  Looking forward to our next trip.
Great food from great people. Absolutely delicious and inexpensive. Great clean place with awesome service.
Best BaBa I'VE ever had ..... Seriously BEST!!!!
Always exceptionally good food.

great food for reasonable price.  Much more pleasant than a couple of years ago, some young manager gave my daughter a hard time because she's allergic to soy, which is in a lot of things.   Tonight was my 1st time back since, and I didn't see that manager. The chips seemed very oily tonight.

Fast service and good Mexican food. 
We eat there quite often when we are in the area. Only complaint my family and I have is we wish their beans a bean dip wasn't made with lard. But we can get whole beans, so that helps a little.

Nothing but 5*****! 
One of the best Mexican food I ever had! 
Best service!!!!
People are rude food was awful

My wife and I go there every Thursday. we call it Taco Thursday. we could go anywhere but it is the best food in town. the Waiters, people who bring the chips, and the checkout guy Sal are always the most friendly and happy to see you every time. The prices are great. We get in and out quick to go back to work
Food was great. Friendly and fast service. Was like being at home. Except ya don't have to clean up!
Love that place. The cook always does a great job. As well as the waitresses. Great food.
It was awesome. It was clean and the food was perfect. Shout out to the cook. Thank you
One of my favorite places to eat. Service is good and the food is almost always great. It's not fancy food so if that's what you are looking for you need to find something else.
Pleasurable experience. Very friendly staff. Me and my granddaughter eat here often.
Awesome specials. Great prices and just a good down home feel
Great food. Great service. Great prices.
Good food, good price, but got order wrong in drive thru
My family loves eating here great food at a great price
Fantastic food, service and prices. I love Chocolate Gravy and it was great! (We live in Texas) would highly recommend for great food!
Great place to eat, fast friendly  service
My favorite slug burgers to buy place
Love a good slug burger😍

Only been a couple times. Both times my burger tasted like it sat in a warmer for hours and put in the microwave to melt the cheese. Fries were cold and soggy. I always see a crowd there so I tried to give it a chance. No luck the few times I’ve been. Probably won’t go back
This is a great get it and go kinda place love getting lunch here.
Fast service... friendly people! Good eating home of the dough- burger ( slug burger) you would just have to give it a try!
The food is really good. Would be really nice if the upgraded the place and had WiFi. Also they don't take debit which really sucks for most customers.
The food is always good. But,  every time we place a large order,  something gets left off and we have to wait til it's fixed or go back. No matter,  we'll always go back.

Hole in the wall diner with decades of grease and good food! Reminds me of the college days loading up with greasy food when we were drunk. Great service and really not so greasy food but greasy. So affordable you can feed a family with $20 bucks. I had to try the slugburger. You better try it too for less than $2 bucks
That's GREAT FOOD ONLY HAD $1 BUT WAS ABLE EAT A BURGER
We drove from Florence, Alabama just to eat here! Love the kolache's and donut's! They have great quality! And are super friendly. I hope they open a store closer to me soon!
Nice thick yet fluffy donuts. Very good.
These donuts are AWESOME!  And the kolachis are pretty great too!
Best donuts in town, I like the glazed donut when it just came out, hot, fresh and delicious..
I always enjoy the food. It is what a doughnut shop should be

My entire family Loves Dilworth’s Hot Tamales!!! They are delicious!!! The staff are professional at all times & just loving people! The tamales have the right amount of spices to hit the spot and the prices are great! Every time  we travel to West TN we make another trip to Dilworth’s!
A rare gem. Great tamales. Wonderful people. This is the real deal. Love it !

I love going back to Corinth and these tamales are a big part of that reason.   I drove in a couple of weekends ago and got three dozen to bring home so we could freeze 2 dozen.  When i told someone I was going to get them she said dilworths is  the only place left.   As if I meant any other place?!  If you've never had them it's worth your time to drive by and get some.   Love the hot ones.

I love this place. When I was younger wasnt my thing but I have been eating for 20 years and is the best no doubt. I no longer live in corinth but best believe if I am close we gotta go to Dilworth's and get extra to freeze when I get home! This is one of my favorite place to eat like ever!!
We drive several hours one way to pick up tamales.  We absolutely think they are the best.
These are the best donuts in town. We get donuts from them for church every week. The employees are very efficient and friendly.
Awesome place with great staff, delicious donuts and yummy breakfast food!
Very good customer service! The food is great. Sometimes they throw in some extra treats on the house.
The place to go to for a quick breakfast. Delicious apple fritters and everything is well priced. Will become a daily spot now!
Donuts are awesome,  the wrap sausage is delicious  open till 1 daily.  I'm getting hungry thinking about this place
